%N A395391 Decimal expansion of the probability that the segment between two points selected independently and uniformly at random in the interior of a regular pentagram is included entirely within that pentagram.
%C A395391 The corresponding probability for a regular hexagram is 23/24 = 0.958333... .
%H A395391 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Pentagram">Pentagram</a>.
%H A395391 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Pentagram.html">Pentagram</a>.
%H A395391 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pentagram">Pentagram</a>.
%H A395391 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A395391 Equals (3-phi)/2 + (2-phi)*log(phi), where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%F A395391 Equals 1 - 1/(2*phi) + log(phi)/phi^2.
%e A395391 0.874789567009452698532553411765476794061908558500247...
%t A395391 RealDigits[1 - 1/(2*GoldenRatio) + Log[GoldenRatio]/GoldenRatio^2, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395391 (PARI) my(phi = quadgen(5)); 1 - 1/(2*phi) + log(phi)/phi^2
%Y A395391 Cf. A001622, A002390.
%Y A395391 Other constants related to the regular pentagram: A134974, A179050, A188593, A348757.
%K A395391 nonn,cons,new
%O A395391 0,1
